==================================================
HISTORICAL AWARD ANALYSIS ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Analyze prior awards in similar:
- NAICS
- PSC/FSC
- agencies
- locations
- contract categories
- solicitation types

The system should identify:
- historical winners
- repeat winners
- incumbent patterns
- award frequencies
- market accessibility

==================================================
WINNER PROFILE ENGINE
==================================================

The system should identify:
- what type of companies win
- maturity level of winners
- operational scale of winners
- common certifications
- supplier relationships
- contract vehicles
- regional dominance

EXAMPLES:
- Defense Prime
- Federal VAR
- Staffing Integrator
- Technical Boutique
- Commodity Supplier
- Research Contractor
- Regional Fulfillment Vendor

==================================================
COMPETITION DENSITY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Determine how crowded or accessible a market is.

ANALYZE:
- average bidder counts
- historical number of offers
- repeat incumbents
- sole-source patterns
- procurement accessibility

EXAMPLES:
- 1 bidder = underserved market
- 40 bidders = saturated commodity market

==================================================
INCUMBENT ANALYSIS ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Identify incumbent lock-in risk.

ANALYZE:
- repeat award patterns
- agency loyalty patterns
- recompete cycles
- incumbent contract duration
- incumbent frequency

OUTPUT:
Incumbent Advantage Score

==================================================
PRICING INTELLIGENCE ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Analyze historical pricing behavior.

ANALYZE:
- average award values
- pricing ranges
- award spread
- LPTA vs best-value awards
- margin patterns
- pricing competitiveness

OUTPUT:
Pricing Benchmark Analysis

