EXAMPLE PRICING OUTPUT
==================================================

{
  "average_award_value": "$180,000",
  "estimated_winning_range": "$160,000-$195,000",
  "pricing_model": "LPTA",
  "pricing_pressure": "High",
  "recommended_margin_range": "8%-14%"
}

==================================================
WIN PROBABILITY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Estimate realistic probability of success.

FACTORS:
- company maturity
- past performance
- incumbent strength
- pricing competitiveness
- competition density
- operational fit
- certifications
- historical winner profiles

OUTPUT:
Win Probability Estimate

==================================================
EXAMPLE OUTPUT
==================================================

{
  "estimated_win_probability": "Low",
  "primary_reasons": [
    "Strong incumbent presence",
    "Mandatory past performance gap",
    "Large operational maturity mismatch"
  ],
  "recommended_strategy": "Subcontractor"
}

==================================================
LOSS ANALYSIS ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Help users understand why bids failed.

POSSIBLE REASONS:
- price too high
- weak past performance
- incumbent advantage
- missing certifications
- poor proposal fit
- insufficient operational maturity
- weak teaming strategy
- unrealistic execution plan

==================================================
EXAMPLE LOSS ANALYSIS
==================================================

{
  "loss_reasons": [
    "Bid price 22% above historical average",
    "Incumbent held prior 3 awards",
    "Missing federal past performance"
  ],
  "recommended_improvements": [
    "Pursue subcontract role first",
    "Build agency-specific history",
    "Improve supplier pricing"
  ]
}

